{"id":63540,"title":"Effective surgical treatment of progressive nodular histiocytosis.","abstract":"Progressive nodular histiocytosis (PNH) is a rare benign self-limiting histiocytic disorder of the skin that is characterised by the progressive appearance of widespread xanthomatous lesions with no spontaneous remission. We operated on a 13-year-old girl with PNH four times with a result that had stabilised the condition at 1 year.","date":"2014-01-16","categories":"Hemic and Lymphatic Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24428162","annotations":[{"name":"Skin","weight":0.675714,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skin"},{"name":"Surgery","weight":0.575295,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Surgery"},{"name":"Lesion","weight":0.495417,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lesion"},{"name":"Disease","weight":0.424967,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disease"},{"name":"Histiocyte","weight":0.345284,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Histiocyte"},{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.341581,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Remission (medicine)","weight":0.187836,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Remission_(medicine)"},{"name":"Benignity","weight":0.147927,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Benignity"},{"name":"Xanthoma","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Xanthoma"},{"name":"Nodule (medicine)","weight":0.0248395,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nodule_(medicine)"},{"name":"National Party of Honduras","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Party_of_Honduras"},{"name":"Progressivism","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Progressivism"},{"name":"Progressive rock","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Progressive_rock"},{"name":"Histiocytosis","weight":0.0140524,"w